Package: sysc-greet
Architecture: any
Depends:
 greetd,
 kitty,
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Recommends:
 gslapper
Suggests:
 swww,
 sway,
 niri,
 hyprland
Description: terminal-based greeter for greetd
 sysc-greet is a TUI greeter for greetd written in Go.
 It runs inside a terminal emulator and supports theming,
 fonts, wallpapers, and animated backgrounds.
 .
 A Wayland compositor is required at runtime, but no specific
 compositor is enforced. Optional background daemons such as
 gSlapper or swww can be used for wallpapers and videos.

Package: sysc-greet-configs
Architecture: all
Depends: sysc-greet
Description: Example greeter configs for sysc-greet
 Example compositor and terminal configs for running sysc-greet
 with greetd (niri, sway, kitty).
 .
 These files are installed as examples under:
   /usr/share/sysc-greet/configs
 and must be copied manually into /etc/greetd or ~/.config.

